---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Recursio"
  description="Recursio Privacy Policy: what data we collect, how it is used, and how to request deletion."
  canonicalSlug="privacy"
>
  <article class="legal-section">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio is a language-learning app that helps users save vocabulary, review words, practice
      grammar, and use AI-assisted learning features. This Privacy Policy explains what information
      Recursio may collect, how it is used, and how users can request deletion of their account
      and learning data.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Account information:</strong> sign-in provider, account identifier, and email address
        if provided by Apple or Google.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Learning data:</strong> saved words, vocabulary spaces, word states, grammar progress,
        practice history, recall progress, Coach sessions, AI Writing attempts, and related learning
        activity.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>AI practice content:</strong> text the user submits to Coach, AI Writing, AI Grammar,
        and similar learning features.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Subscription status:</strong> plan level (PRACTICE, SMART, or PRO), entitlement status,
        and store-related subscription identifiers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Technical data:</strong> app version, device/platform type, crash or diagnostic
        information if enabled later.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Note:</strong> Recursio does not directly collect payment card details. Payments are
        processed by the App Store or Google Play.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide saved vocabulary and learning progress.</li>
      <li>To personalize recall, grammar, and Coach practice.</li>
      <li>To generate AI feedback, explanations, and practice tasks.</li>
      <li>To manage subscription access.</li>
      <li>To improve reliability and fix technical issues.</li>
      <li>To respond to support requests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. AI Processing</h2>
    <p>
      Some user-submitted text may be processed by AI service providers to generate feedback,
      corrections, explanations, practice prompts, or conversation responses. Users should not
      submit sensitive personal information in practice answers. AI feedback may be imperfect and
      should be treated as learning assistance, not as a guaranteed authoritative correction.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
    <p>
      Subscription purchases are handled by Apple App Store or Google Play. Recursio receives
      subscription entitlement information needed to unlock paid features, but does not receive
      full payment card details.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio does not sell user personal data. Data may be shared only with service providers
      needed to operate the app, such as authentication providers, hosting providers, AI processing
      providers, app store payment systems, or support tools.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      Account-linked learning data is retained while the user account remains active, unless the
      user requests deletion or unless retention is required for legal, security, or operational
      reasons.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Account and Data Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Users can request deletion of their account and account-linked learning data through the
      <a href="/delete-account">Delete Account page</a> or by contacting
      <a href="mailto:support@recursio.app">support@recursio.app</a>. Deletion requests are
      processed within a reasonable period, typically within 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Children</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio is not intended for children under 13. If a parent or guardian believes a child has
      provided personal information, they should contact support.
    </p>

    <h2>10. International Users</h2>
    <p>
      Data may be processed in countries other than the user's country of residence, depending on
      service providers.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio may update this Privacy Policy. The "Last updated" date will be changed when the
      policy is updated.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:support@recursio.app">support@recursio.app</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</LegalLayout>
